BARD ARCHETYPES

At guild level 10, Bards can choose a performance archetype:

  specialize
  specialize <archetype>

Your first choice is free. Changing archetypes later costs coin, because it
requires relearning how you structure a performance.

Archetypes change the feel and mechanics of Bard songs and older Bard skills.
They can affect Performance gains, song-field strength, field duration with
favored instruments, hidden harmony resonance, role songs, social reputation
work, control songs, Finales, and the flavor of your performances.

Current archetypes:

  War Conductor
    Tactical battle support. Rhythm and Harmony gain more momentum and stronger
    fields, especially with drums, horn, or war harp. Certain hidden harmonies
    resolve with a sharper command of formation and tempo. Rally, Hero,
    follower songs, and other support moments benefit from this style.

  Shadow Minstrel
    Control, misdirection, and emotional pressure. Melody and Dissonance gain
    more momentum and stronger morale pressure, especially with flute, chimes,
    or violin. Some hidden harmonies gain shadowed, misleading resolutions.
    Soothe, Otto, Defame, and other control or social tricks benefit from this
    style.

  Skald
    Aggressive combat performance. Rhythm and Crescendo hit harder, especially
    with drums, horn, or war harp. Active song fields can add skaldic sound
    damage in combat, and some hidden harmonies become battle cries. Wail,
    singing weapons, follower songs, and direct pressure benefit from this
    style.

  Virtuoso
    Mastery through precision. Your song-chain memory extends, allowing longer
    hidden chains. Complex chains and favored instruments such as concert lute,
    violin, and chimes improve field power and momentum. Study, lore, craft,
    and precision-based command moments benefit from this style.

  Doom Singer
    Dissonance, dread, and morale warfare. Dissonance and Finale performances
    gain more pressure, especially with violin, war harp, or chimes. Certain
    hidden harmonies resolve into colder and more terrible patterns. Wail,
    Villain, Battlefield Silence, and enemy morale pressure benefit from this
    style.

Use bscore to see your current archetype.

Choosing an archetype is a playstyle decision:

  Pick War Conductor if you like directing a party.
  Pick Shadow Minstrel if you like control and misdirection.
  Pick Skald if you want aggressive combat music.
  Pick Virtuoso if you want precision and complex chains.
  Pick Doom Singer if you want dread, pressure, and Finales.

